added.title: Tooned In Space
added.description: The toons take Marvin the Martian's class, and head to space. Buster tries to cheer up a homesick Babs, Plucky searches for a space outfit, and Sweetie is too obsessed with a video game to notice any of it - even when the aliens attack!

added.title: Freshman Orientoontion
added.description: It's the first day of school at Acme Looniversity - the Harvard of being stupid - where we find fraternal twins, Babs and Buster Bunny meeting their new friends - tough chick Sweetie Bird, self-effacing sweetheart Hamton J. Pig, and narcissist clown, Plucky Duck. These young dreamers all share the same big plans - to learn how to be  professional toons -  and their journey begins now.

added.title: The Prince and the Blobby Princess
added.description: Princess Syllabob, the blobby daughter of Axalotly, King of the Deep, has been carried off by a gang of gulls and discarded on the forest floor. Prince Ivandoe and Bert happen upon her and agree to escort the Princess back to the lake before she dehydrates. Overcoming obstacles, including a swan-napping by Prince Svan, Ivandoe and Syllabob develop... well, a sort of... friendship?
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Wise Wizard of Wisdom
added.description: Struck down by a poisonous turnip, Prince Ivandoe & Bert must seek a cure from the Wise Wizard of Wisdom. They set off, and along the way, they are joined by an equally desperate small-faced bear, a bunny-dragon, and a truly useless fairy. Once they reach the Wise Wizard however, they discover that he is a lot less wise and a lot more "sassy" than anyone could have predicted!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Squeak of Obedience
added.description: Feral and her gang of cat-thieves have stolen Prince Ivandoe's map to Eagle Mountain. Cupcake, the pink-poodle survivalist offers to train Prince Ivandoe to become a Jungle Warrior. So that together they can infiltrate Feral's camp and get back whats theirs. For Feral also stole a precious item from Cupcake... one that exerts a strange hold over him - "The Squeak of Obedience!"
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: Me, My Elf, and I
added.description: Duncan tricks Chef into taking the class to the North Pole in order to remove his name from the naughty list.

added.title: Space Codyty
added.description: Izzy, convinced that Cody is an alien, embarks on a journey through space to take him back home.

added.title: Yes Dude Yes
added.description: Mordecai wants to find a new girl to get over Margaret.

added.title: Busted Cart
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby bust up the cart while doing stunts and have to figure out a way to fix it.

added.title: Dead at Eight
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to babysit Death's kid.

added.title: Access Denied
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to go to Margaret's birthday party at an exclusive club.

added.title: Muscle Mentor
added.description: Rigby gets mentored by Muscle Man.

added.title: Trucker Hall of Fame
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Muscle Man get to the Big Rig Museum to spread his dad's hat's ashes.

added.title: Out of Commission
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have one last day with the cart before they have to get rid of it.

added.title: Fancy Restaurant
added.description: Muscle Man has to impress his girlfriend's parents at a fancy dinner.

added.title: Diary
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to fix a lock on Margaret's diary before she gets back from a weekend trip.

added.title: The Best VHS in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to return an overdue VHS to the store so they won't be banned from renting new movies.

added.title: Polly's New Crew
added.description: The bears reunite with their old friend Polly the Pirate Captain. They soon learn that Polly is under the effect of a pirate curse and need to help them overcome it.

added.title: Vengeance of Vilgax Part 1
added.description: Armed with the power of 10 Alien Champions, Vilgax sets his sites on Earth. And the only hero standing in his way Is Ben Tennyson.

added.title: Vengeance of Vilgax Part 2
added.description: In the conclusion of this epic battle, Vilgax battles an array of Aliens and is close to ending Ben forever. But Diamondhead has different plans.

added.title: Inferno
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Kevin investigate the explosion of a mysterious machine, unleashing hundreds of rock eating aliens. Not good news for Kevin!

added.title: Fool's Gold
added.description: When an alien named Orb asks for help finding his missing friend, Decka, Ben, Gwen and Kevin are surprised to learn just how valuable a friend he is.

added.title: Simple
added.description: When Ben arrives on a distant planet to try and help broker peace between warring factions, he ends up transforming into a new alien named Lodestar.

added.title: Can't Stop the Martians/Best Nest Test
added.description: The Martians come to Pretty Big City but find themselves in need of help when they are unable to land their spaceship./Zee needs to communicate with Sif in outer space but can't because a bird has made its home on top of the satellite dish!

added.title: Funshine's Un-fun Day
added.description: Funshine can't bring himself to tell Cheer he accidentally broke her beloved necklace. His attempts to repair the broken necklace end in failure, so he hides it. When Cheer wrongly thinks Dibble is responsible for the disappearance of the necklace, Funshine knows he must tell her the truth.

added.title: A Work of Parts
added.description: Grady fills a big crack in the park's entryway with concrete so no one trips. Vivie comes up with the idea to add found items, creating a beautiful art piece and discovers that even though she's small she can have a big effect on the park.

added.title: Big Rig Bam
added.description: Bam must learn to adapt and try something new as he's tasked to dive the Bat Big Rig all the way to Star City, while the Legion of Zoom chases after him.

added.title: Flight of the Kitty
added.description: Now that Catwoman has equipped Kitty with wings, Batwing tries to teach the easily-distracted Kitty how to fly.

added.title: A Tale of Two Bibis
added.description: Badcomputer captures Bibi and disguises Jestah to take her place with the Batwheels so that Jestah can steal the Batcomputer's motherboard. Can Bibi get free in time to unmask the imposter and save the day?

added.title: That's the Way the Windmill Blows!/Mecha Machine Makers!
added.description: The windmill isn't turning, which means Sunny Field Farm has no power. The windmill needs to turn again so Zee can launch his rocket!/Izzy and Timmy are making a bird caller for Grandma, but have trouble connecting pieces of their machine.

added.title: A Yoorg Awakening
added.description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

added.title: Return of the Gnomes
added.description: When Gus and Garth's greedy uncle makes his nephews forget the caring, sharing, and generosity they learned from the Care Bears and convinces them to return to their old selfish ways, the Bears must help them remember their caring hearts.
